body:
@av8ramit 

I am am pretty sure I am nvidia-docker2, which I use daily, and it still has the alias so you do not have to do `--runtime=nvidia` that is only needed if you want to trigger is without the alias. But their docuemtnation says to use what @chrish42 states.   

Change the install to indicate nvidia-docker2 and go ahead and change the command to `docker run --runtime=nvidia` since that is how nvidia [documents](https://github.com/nvidia/nvidia-docker/wiki/Installation-(version-2.0)) it.  Both may work but no reason to deviate from their instructions.
